Description: Special Technique/Craft:Kalamkari is a type of hand-painted or block-printed cotton textile, wherein motifs are inspired by the folklore and are hand-painted using the tool of kalam directly onto the fabric. The process involves washing, rinsing, soaking and bleaching the fabric and applying mordants and dyes using natural substances like indigo (blue), madder (red), mango bark (yellow) and palm sugar (black). Painting on the fabric is done with a kalam, charcoal and myrobalan paste.Design:Region: Andhra Pradesh and Madhya PradeshBlackStraight kurta with Kalamkari hand-block printMandarin collarLong sleeves with roll-up tabsButton closureCraft: Kalamkari Hand block printDisclaimer:This is a handcrafted kurta and is prone to colour bleeding due to the use of natural dyes The print on the garment might be uneven owing to the handcrafted nature of the product, adding essence to the garment.

ProductName: Taavi Men Maroon Kalamkari Block Printed Straight Sustainable Kurta with Roll-Up Sleeves
ProductBrand: Taavi
Gender: Men
Price (INR): 1299
Description: Special Technique/Craft:Kalamkari is a type of hand-painted or block-printed cotton textile, wherein motifs are inspired by the folklore and are hand-painted using the tool of kalam directly onto the fabric. The process involves washing, rinsing, soaking and bleaching the fabric and applying mordants and dyes using natural substances like indigo (blue), madder (red), mango bark (yellow) and palm sugar (black). Painting on the fabric is done with a kalam, charcoal and myrobalan paste.Design:Region: Andhra Pradesh and Madhya PradeshMaroonStraight kurta with Kalamkari hand-block printMandarin collarLong sleeves with roll-up tabsButton closureCraft: Kalamkari Hand block printDisclaimer:This is a handcrafted kurta and is prone to colour bleeding due to the use of natural dyes The print on the garment might be uneven owing to the handcrafted nature of the product, adding essence to the garment.

ProductID: 10184939
ProductName: Taavi Men Red Kalamkari Block Printed Straight Sustainable Kurta with Roll-Up Sleeves
ProductBrand: Taavi
Gender: Men
Price (INR): 1299
Description: Special Technique/Craft:Kalamkari is a type of hand-painted or block-printed cotton textile, wherein motifs are inspired by the folklore and are hand-painted using the tool of kalam directly onto the fabric. The process involves washing, rinsing, soaking and bleaching the fabric and applying mordants and dyes using natural substances like indigo (blue), madder (red), mango bark (yellow) and palm sugar (black). Painting on the fabric is done with a kalam, charcoal and myrobalan paste.Design:Region: Andhra Pradesh and Madhya PradeshRedStraight kurta with Kalamkari hand-block printMandarin collarLong sleeves with roll-up tabsButton closureOne patch pocketCraft: Kalamkari Hand block printDisclaimer:This is a handcrafted kurta and is prone to colour bleeding due to the use of natural dyes The print on the garment might be uneven owing to the handcrafted nature of the product, adding essence to the garment.
PrimaryColor:  Red

Description: Special Technique/Craft:Kalamkari is a type of hand-painted or block-printed cotton textile, wherein motifs are inspired from the folklore and are hand painted using the tool of kalam directly onto the fabric. The process involves washing, rinsing, soaking and bleaching the fabric and applying mordants and dyes using natural substances like indigo (blue), madder (red), mango bark (yellow) and palm sugar (black). Painting on the fabric is done with a kalam, charcoal and myrobalan paste.Design:Region: Andhra Pradesh and Madhya PradeshRust orangeHand block printed A-line topMandarin collarHalf button placketThree-quarter sleevesPleated Kalamkari hand block printDisclaimer:This is a handcrafted top, and is prone to colour bleeding due to use of natural dyesThe print on the garment might be uneven- owing to the handcrafted nature of the product, adding essence to the garment.

The main tools of the printer are wooden blocks in different shapes - square, rectangle, oval, round and semi-circular or crescent - and sizes called bunta. Blocks are hand-carved of seasoned teak wood by trained craftsmen. The blocks for imprinting are hand-carved by skilled artisans in wood. Description: Kalamkari is a type of hand-painted or block-printed cotton textile, wherein motifs are inspired from the folklore and are hand painted using the tool of kalam directly onto the fabric. The process involves washing, rinsing, soaking and bleaching the fabric and applying mordants and dyes using natural substances like indigo (blue), madder (red), mango bark (yellow) and palm sugar (black). Description: About the shoeBack in the '80s, Ralph Sampson was a basketball legend. First pick of the NBA Draft in '83, Rookie of the Year in '84, he towered over the rest of the players and elevated the game to unprecedented heights. Signing Sampson took PUMA to the next level in the basketball world - and in return, we created a customized kick just for him. Enter: the PUMA Ralph Sampson. With a mid-height construction for ankle support and a lightweight design for speed and agility, it was tailored to Sampson's needs on the court and stamped with his signature at the side. Today, over 30 years later, PUMA is bringing back the OG silhouette in honor of a Hall of Famer whose legend still impacts the game today.
